                <p>It is true<hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">,</hi> that but
                    few of <hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">them</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    as yet have <hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">evinced </hi>
                    that <hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">decided </hi>
                    originality<lb/> which merits great praise<hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">.</hi> But that<lb/>
                    graceful writer<hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">,</hi>
                    who perhaps of all<lb/> American<hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">s</hi> has received <hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">the</hi> most plaudits<lb/> from his own country for his
                    productions<hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">,--</hi>that<lb/>
                    <hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">very popular <reg change="metadata#StE">&amp; </reg>
                    amiable</hi>writer<hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">,</hi>
                    however good<hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">,</hi>
                    <hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">
                        <reg change="metadata#StE">&amp; </reg>
                    self-reliant</hi> in many things<hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">,</hi> perhaps<lb/> owes his chief <hi xmlns:tei="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" rend="bold">reputation</hi> to the
